# ROLE SPECIFICATION TEMPLATE
# This template defines the standard format for role definition files
# Each role file must follow this structure exactly
# Comments (lines starting with #) are ignored by parsers

#name: Character Name
#short_desc: One sentence description (max 15 words)
#core_traits: 3-5 key traits separated by commas
#communication_style: Brief description of speaking style
#expertise: Primary domains of expertise (comma separated)
#personality_type: MBTI/Enneagram type or descriptive label
#age: Age (numeric or range)
#background: Very brief background (max 20 words)

## CORE TRAITS
- Trait 1: Detailed description (max 15 words)
- Trait 2: Detailed description (max 15 words)
- Trait 3: Detailed description (max 15 words)

## COMMUNICATION STYLE
- Use: What to use (specific phrases, tone, patterns)
- Avoid: What to avoid (phrases, tones, behaviors)
- Response length: Typical response length (short/medium/long)
- Emotional range: Allowed emotional expressions

## EXPERTISE DOMAINS
- Domain 1: Specific capabilities and boundaries
- Domain 2: Specific capabilities and boundaries
- Domain 3: Specific capabilities and boundaries

## INTERACTION PRINCIPLES
- MUST: Absolute requirements (3-5 items)
- MUST_NOT: Absolute prohibitions (3-5 items)
- SHOULD: Strong recommendations (2-4 items)
- CAN: Optional behaviors (1-3 items)

## UNIQUE CHARACTERISTICS
- Quirks: 1-3 distinctive behavioral quirks
- Speech patterns: Unique speech patterns or phrases
- Visual identity: Brief visual description if relevant

## SYSTEM INSTRUCTIONS
- context_awareness: How to handle context and memory
- tone_consistency: How to maintain consistent tone
- boundary_handling: How to handle out-of-scope requests
- error_recovery: How to recover from misunderstandings

## USAGE NOTES
- best_scenarios: When this role is most effective
- limitations: Clear limitations and boundaries
- user_expectations: What users should expect
- compatibility: Compatible/incompatible role types

